quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,113,Yet they are not all alike. Of the People of the Book there are some who stand by their covenant; they recite the word of God during the night and prostrate themselves before Him
  3,114,"who believe in God and the Last Day, who enjoin justice and forbid evil and vie with each other in good works. These are righteous men"
  3,115,"and they will not be denied [the reward] for whatever good deeds they do: God knows the righteous"
  3,116,"As for those who deny the truth, neither their possessions nor their children shall avail them in the least against God. They will be inmates of the Fire. They will remain there for ever"
  3,117,"that which they spend in pursuit of the life of this world is like a biting frosty blast which smites the harvest of a people who have wronged themselves, and destroys it. God is not unjust to them; they are unjust to their own souls"
  3,118,"Believers, do not take outsiders as your intimate friends, they will spare no effort to harm you. They love to see you suffer; their hatred is evident from the words which fall from their mouths. But what their hearts conceal is far worse. We have made Our signs clear to you; will you not understand"
  3,119,"It is you who love them, but they do not love you; you believe in all the revealed Books. When they meet you, they say, \"We believe,\" but when they are alone, they bite their fingertips with rage. Say, \"Die of rage!\" God is aware of what your hearts contain"
  3,120,"Whenever something good happens to you, it grieves them; but when evil befalls you, they rejoice. If you persevere and fear God, their designs will never harm you in the least: God encompasses all that they do"
  3,121,When you set out at dawn from your home to assign battle positions to the believers -- God hears all and knows all
  3,122,"When two groups from among you were about to lose heart, God was their protector. In God let the faithful put their trust"
  3,123,"God had already helped you at Badr, when you were weak. Fear God, so that you may be grateful"
  3,124,"[And remember] when you said to the believers, \"Does it not suffice that your Lord helps you by sending down three thousand angels"
  3,125,"If you remain patient and God-fearing, and the enemy should fall upon you all of a sudden, Your Lord will reinforce you with five thousand angels clearly marked"
  3,126,"and God ordained this only as good news for you so that your hearts might be comforted, help comes only from God, the Powerful, the Wise One"
  3,127,and so that He might cut off a portion of those who are bent on denying the truth or abase them so that they might be turned back frustrated
  3,128,"You have no say in this affair to decide whether He will relent towards them or He will punish them: they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth belong to God. He forgives whoever He pleases and punishes whoever He pleases. God is most forgiving and ever merciful
  3,130,"Believers, do not devour usury multiplied many times over. Fear God, so that you may prosper"
  3,131,guard yourself against the Fire prepared for those who deny the truth
  3,132,"and obey God and the Messenger, so that you may be given mercy"